author: Spencer Jakab
title: The Jobs Report and Stocks: What’s Not to Hate?
text:
There are tens of thousands of people working in finance who have never experienced a Federal Reserve rate increase. Friday’s jobs report did nothing to convince them or their older colleagues whether that 9½-year wait will end this month.
Payroll growth was somewhat tepid at 173,000 jobs, below expectations for 220,000. But there was a healthy drop in the unemployment rate and gain in wages. That made for a split decision. Stock...
